JO  - The Quarterly Journal of Economics
JA  - Q J Econ
VL  - 107
IS  - 3
SP  - 985
EP  - 1002
SN  - 0033-5533
AB  - The microeconomic forces that influence real wages are not fully understood. This paper studies pay determination using data on approximately 600 labor contracts. It finds that the real wage is an increasing function of past profitability in the employer's industry, and a decreasing function of the level of unemployment in the employer's region. These results are consistent with rent-sharing theories.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
