JO  - The Quarterly Journal of Economics
JA  - Q J Econ
VL  - 107
IS  - 3
SP  - 819
EP  - 863
SN  - 0033-5533
AB  - This study measures the heterogeneity of establishment-level employment changes in the U. S. manufacturing sector over the 1972 to 1986 period. We measure this heterogeneity in terms of the gross creation and destruction of jobs and the rate at which jobs are reallocated across plants. Our measurement efforts enable us to quantify the connection between job reallocation and worker reallocation, to evaluate theories of heterogeneity in plant-level employment dynamics, and to establish new results related to the cyclical behavior of the labor market.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
